org.apache.freemarker.core.model.impl

Class DefaultObjectWrapperConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.freemarker.core.model.impl.DefaultObjectWrapperConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultObjectWrapperBuilder

    public abstract class DefaultObjectWrapperConfiguration
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    Holds DefaultObjectWrapper configuration settings and defines their defaults. You will not use this abstract class directly, but concrete subclasses like DefaultObjectWrapperBuilder. Unless, you are developing a builder for a custom DefaultObjectWrapper subclass. In that case, note that overriding the equals(java.lang.Object) and hashCode() is important, as these objects are used as ObjectWrapper singleton lookup keys.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DefaultObjectWrapperConfiguration

        protected DefaultObjectWrapperConfiguration(Version incompatibleImprovements,
                                            boolean isIncompImprsAlreadyNormalized)
        Parameters:
        incompatibleImprovements - See the corresponding parameter of DefaultObjectWrapper.DefaultObjectWrapper(Version). Not null. Note that the version will be normalized to the lowest version where the same incompatible DefaultObjectWrapper improvements were already present, so for the returned instance getIncompatibleImprovements() might returns a lower version than what you have specified here.
        isIncompImprsAlreadyNormalized - Tells if the incompatibleImprovements parameter contains an already normalized value. This parameter meant to be true when the class that extends DefaultObjectWrapper needs to add additional breaking versions over those of DefaultObjectWrapper. Thus, if this parameter is true, the versions where DefaultObjectWrapper had breaking changes must be already factored into the incompatibleImprovements parameter value, as no more normalization will happen. (You can use DefaultObjectWrapper.normalizeIncompatibleImprovementsVersion(Version) to discover those.)
        Since:
        2.3.22
